Belgium: Political crisis: Conspiracy of Nobles and Siege of Maastricht prompt Isabella Clara Eugenia, Governess General of the Spanish Netherlands, to summon the final session of the Estates General.
Cambodia: Ponhea Tu killed after rebelling against the Ubhayoraj. Followed by his younger half-brother Ponhea Nur
China: The later Jin dynasty conquered Inner Mongolia.
Estonia: Foundation of the University of Tartu under Swedish king Gustavus Adolphus.
Germany: Battle of Lützen: Forces led by the Swedish Empire defeated forces under the command of the Holy Roman Empire near Lützen. The Swedish king Gustavus Adolphus was killed.
Philippine: Lorenzo de Olaza appointed Governor-General (1632–1633) by the Audiencia Real.
Russia: Smolensk War: With the expiration of the Truce of Deulino, a Muscovite army was sent to lay siege to Smolensk.
Sweden: The Battle of Lützen takes place. King Gustav II Adolf is killed in battle.
USA: The Province of Maryland was founded.
